## Routing

- Use the App Router (not Pages Router)
- Colocate page-specific components in the route directory
- Use layout.tsx for shared layouts
- Use loading.tsx for Suspense boundaries
- Use error.tsx for error boundaries

## Components

- Server Components by default
- Add "use client" directive only for: event handlers, useState, useEffect, browser APIs
- Keep client components small and leaf-level
- Pass server data as props to client components

## Data Fetching

- Use Server Actions for mutations (forms, button actions)
- Use server components for data reads
- Cache with unstable_cache or React cache when appropriate
- Revalidate with revalidatePath / revalidateTag

## File Conventions

- page.tsx — route page
- layout.tsx — shared layout
- loading.tsx — loading UI
- error.tsx — error boundary
- not-found.tsx — 404 page
